The past few weeks, I’ve felt overwhelmed..

Lots of work to do, frustrated by not being able to go home for the holidays due to poor planning, health and motivation has slipped up a bit due to being sick etc…

Which caused me to think a lot.. just like sit in my thoughts for second.. what do I want out of this life I have? 

Ultimately for me, I want to make an impact.. I want to help other people whether that be through fitness or helping people grow their business and impact others.. I feel the intention is the same. I want to help people live better lives, become happy with the life they have created for themselves, and ultimately live positively so that it inspires others to live that way too. 

My overwhelm comes from falling short of my goals on some levels. My words for the new year are: “fearless” and “action”. But what does that mean? 🤔 

So many times I’ve stopped myself from showing up to my full potential because I’m afraid of failing or what other people will think. Either that, or I simply just haven’t taken action on my plans. 

The time seems to go by in fast motion lately, and I want to make sure I’m using every day to take action in a fearless way to feel accomplished with my goals. 

If I seem different.. it’s because I decided to stop wasting so much time. 

Do you guys resonate with this? How are you feeling about what you’ve done with 2022? How will you be different in 2023?⬇️

There is no elevator to success. 🏙 You have to take the stairs.

What does that mean? You can’t teleport to your goals. 

It’s small steps of action every day. That’s what gets you to where you want to be. Small, consistent action.

If you feel frustrated by not having reached your goals yet… it’s because you haven’t been consistent long enough. Keep going.

How I found strength in weakness. 

The things that broke me once, have strengthened me..

*THESE ARE PHOTOS FROM MY PAST. ♥️🫶 But I wanted to share my story… 

Here are some moments that knocked me down vs. the beautiful things that came from them:

🥊 Abuse/ Toxic relationships-> I learned how to set boundaries and walk away from toxic people. 

😢 loneliness & starting over when I moved to California-> I grew confidence and independence and met some incredible people I would have never gotten to meet if I hadn’t moved here. 

🍷 Substance abuse-> I learned not to par take in things that don’t serve me, and have dialed back on the drinking and partying/ embarrassing myself/ putting myself in danger. 

💼Job loss-> I was crushed at the time and fell into depression, but found much better opportunities as a result of it and am so happy because of it. 

🙇🏼‍♀️body dysmorphia-> I still struggle with this, but I went from eating 600 calories a day and running 6 miles, to learning to prioritize the right foods and found weight training as a saving grace that made me fall in love with getting stronger and is now my daily routine. 

We all have struggles to overcome or “shadows” of our past selves we are trying to hide or heal from. 

In chapter 2023, I hope we can all take our struggles and let them become lessons and tools used to strengthen who we want to become.

The “I eat healthy but I can’t lose weight” starter pack

Top 5 reasons you are sabotaging your weight loss even though you think you’re eating “healthy”. 

1) Drinking alcohol throughout the week - alcohol has empty calories with no nutritional value, makes your restrain water weight, and disrupts liver function (your liver breaks down fats)

2) The oils you cook with and sauces you put on your food- Use a spray cooking oil instead of dousing your food in oil to significantly cut down on calories. Same with sauces.. if you’re not reading the label to check the nutrition facts, and measuring your serving size, you’re likely dumping hundreds of fats/ sugars/ calories / sodium into the food you think is being served “healthy”

3) You are not measuring your protein/ Carbs
Or have never tracked or weighed what you eat. This is sooo important to not only to make sure you are hitting your protein goals, but to make sure you’re actually eating as much as you think you are.. while it’s not something that should be obsessive or forever.. measuring your food initially educates yourself on what is appropriate to fuel your body and you eventually get a feel for what that looks like, but can only master it through doing it for a while. 

4) Mindless snacking throughout the day- especially processed foods. If you’re snacking out of boredom.. you likely are not eating enough during “meals” or have picked up a bad habit of just eating because something is there, not because you’re hungry.. identify the issue, and don’t keep junk around! 

5) You’re just straight up eating too much- science tells us that you have to be in a caloric deficit to lose weight. So even if you are eating healthy food choices.. it’s about how much you are eating. If you haven’t measured your food, you are simply guessing.. and this is probably the biggest reason behind why people get frustrated from not losing weight.. because they “think” they are making healthy food choices .. but are in actuality just eating too much of those healthy foods.

Do any of these sound like you? Comment below if you learned something here. 👇🏽

I know cold plunging has been around for a minute, but I had zero interest in trying it as I am pretty cold intolerant and couldn’t understand why anyone would willingly want to do that to themselves.. seemed insanely uncomfortable for no apparent reason other than some mild health benefits if performed over time… 

But I showed up @superbloom.collective wellness event and thought to myself… you know what? You aren’t trying that because it seems “uncomfortable”… and that’s a really whack excuse not to try something!! So I did.. I made myself try it.. 

I went into it thinking.. “you won’t be able to stay in there but maybe 10 seconds.. but just do that much and get out.” 

With the help of my awesome breathwork guide, Brendan.. the thoughts I told myself in the beginning were proven wrong after staying a full 3 minutes straight! 

How many thoughts do you tell yourself you aren’t capable of doing throughout your day to day?? We constantly try to protect ourselves as humans from pain or harm.. it’s a natural reaction to try to make life as comfortable as possible… but we ultimately end up limiting what we are truly capable of when we stay in our places of what we know and “comfort”. 

Let this be a reminder that there is so much beauty on the other side of our comfort zones.. we are truly limitless when we set our minds to things and overcome that voice that tells us to stay small and that we are not capable. That voice is a liar.

Everything is good. Life is good.... I’m definitely blessed and grateful..however, I think it’s normal to go through certain periods in life when you feel a little “off” or not yourself and no one really talks about that on here.

Haven’t felt as sparkly and energetic as of late.. and haven’t felt up to sharing what I normally share so I wanted to talk about that. 

Typically in life when you feel a little off, it’s because the universe (God), is telling you that you can be and do more. 

You get a chance to step outside of what you’ve always been doing.. and see how you’d like to improve yourself or your situation.

Anyway, If you’re also going through a chapter that feels foreign to you or you don’t feel the “sparkle” that you normally feel.. just know that good things are coming when you take the time to work on yourself, listen and tune in with what is meant for you.

Y’all want to know the “secret” for having a “fit” physique? It’s being hungry to grow. Training like an athlete. Picking up heavier weights with the hopes to get stronger each session, and showing up until you are.

Sitting in front of a computer for 8 hrs per day 5 days per week is not ideal for staying fit… but we make it work in this modern society. 🤓 

3 tips for staying in shape as a busy professional :

1) Meal prep your food 🍱-

This way is not only cheaper but you’ll end up staying within your allotted macros and calorie range

2) Hydrate 💦-
I try to make it a point to drink at least 60oz of water throughout the work day to stay hydrated and keep snack cravings at bay/ avoid sugary energy drinks

3) Schedule your workouts 📅-

Be realistic and stick with a training regimen 5x per week. What can you actually commit to? Be realistic with your schedule and make it a priority. The more convenient it is for you the more likely you are to do it! I try to workout either in my work building gym immediately after work, or drive close by to one on the way home. 

Don’t let work responsibilities stop you from reaching your health goals. What other tips do you guys want to see? 😎

Fun fact: This is not what I’m doing right now.

Another fun fact: 
I actually don’t drink during the week (except maybe a special occasion) 

I try to keep regular alcohol intake down to a minimum of vacations and 1x per week on the weekends if any.

I’m not saying that’s supreme. I’m not condemning anything otherwise.. but I like to think of that as balance in my mind these days.

And I haven’t always had that mindset. I used to either be “balls to the wall” crazy restrictive or polar opposite in college going out for thirsty Thursday all through the weekend.

I for sure live my life and indulge in things but I’m also conscious of the majority of what I intake in my day to day. 

Personally I think too much of anything is a bad thing. For me that means stressing too much over restricting, or cutting things out completely.. to overindulging and having the “treat yo self” mindset like every day. 

Treats taste a little sweeter when you don’t have them all the time and your body kind of loves you for being kind to it the majority of the time. 

I just feel like people typically are shocked about my diet when they find out I don’t eat lettuce every meal and drink casually.. but you don’t have to be a psycho to stay in shape and still live yo life, queen!

We are all guilty of it… 

“I’ll be happy when…..”

I get that promotion 
I get 6 pack abs
I make 6 figures
I find the perfect partner 
I buy an ocean front home
I make my parents proud
I become famous 

The list goes on. 

As humans we are practically created to want more. All the time. We want perfection, and strive for it in every way… and then become disappointed when we fall short. 

But what if we enjoyed where we are now? Like actually took a moment to be insanely happy without giving into thoughts like “it could be better”.. 

I hope this post is a reminder to enjoy the journey. We are all seeking more & probably always will be.. but appreciate the moment in front of you. You will never be in it again.

It’s come to my attention that people who live incredible lives and achieve great things take action. 

That is the sole thing that separates people who accomplish a life they want from people who wish they did. 

It’s not being perfect and nailing it on the first try… 

It’s small, consistent actions. 

Most people (myself included) fear taking action on their goals because they think it’s a waste of time. They fear other people will think they are a joke… and then they themselves will think they are a joke. 

One quote that stands out to me is “whether you think you can or you can’t, you’re right.” 

Believing that you are capable and taking actions towards what you Want to do may not feel natural or intimidating, but without action, one thing is for certain… it will NEVER happen. 

I plan to take action on my bigger picture for myself these next months despite fear of failure or judgement from others. 

Life is short. Believe you can. Take the action, and go for it. The only thing between you and your dreams for your life is action. You got this. 💪🏽

I’m tired of withholding my story, because I know someone out there is struggling with this too. 

I’m not perfect. FAR from it. Things that used to trigger me still do! But I’m proud of the progress I’ve made and how much stronger I have become. 

It took me a LOT of years to come to a place where I feel more at peace with not only my body, but the peace of who I am and am becoming. She’s strong. She’s a force, and she’s essentially limitless when she isn’t in her own head doubting herself. We are so much more than the shells our souls live in. But for our souls to shine, we need to treat and honor our bodies in a way that allows us to shine from the inside out.

I want that realization for you. If you needed to see this today, I hope you remember that you are enough just as you are while on the journey to your strongest self. 

As someone who used to withhold from the basic essential human need of eating because I didn’t think I was worthy enough.. to someone who is proud of my journey and how far I’ve come not only in my difficult life situations, but my physical journey.. I have to say.. I have come so far! I think people think it’s egotistical to show pride in yourself, but as someone who has struggled with extreme mental lows, I’m happy to be seeing my journey from eyes on the other side. 

I hope you can also feel that peace within yourself if you don’t. It’s a beautiful place to be.

THIS. IS. SPARTAHHHH!!!” 

Did my first ever Spartan race yesterday and I’ve gotta say, it was fun!!! I love pushing my body to see what I still have in the tank these days and competing in some friendly competition. I was right along side some marines and it was definitely pushing me to go hard and finish the race strong! 

This definitely won’t be my last one.. but I plan to actually train for the next one and see how strong I can complete it! During events like these.. it’s all a race between you and the clock and mental endurance to not quit when it gets tough… and I really enjoy being in that moment and taking whatever I think I’m capable of and pushing it a bit further.

I feel like not many people talk about this… 

We are always fluctuating through different ups and downs in life and emotions that contribute to our moods and motivation. 

One thing that remains consistent for me throughout those happenings is training… regardless of negative or positive experiences in life.. showing up to train without a doubt lifts my spirits and I find so much mental strength to overcome whatever else is going on in my day to day stresses. 

After recently being sick and throwing out my back.. Every-time I show up, I become more thankful for my health on a regular basis and how good it feels just to be able to show up, move my body and help it grow a little stronger every day. 

Just thankful for this habit in my life that helps me so much in my day to day and my general health. You never appreciate something more until it’s gone or you don’t have it for a while!

I remember when I used to stress over getting a morning coffee that tasted good because I didn’t understand how to have balance in my own life. I obsessively tracked every calorie..Like I would purposely make myself drink black coffee which tastes like battery acid because I was afraid of the calories. 😂

And yes, sugars, carbs fats and excess calories are in a coffee shop latte.. if you’re desperately trying to lose a few pounds, maybe try replacing that with something more low cal..to help you get to goal..but I’m not in excess in my diet and don’t have to worry about the stress of a 150 cal latte in the morning 😂. Realistically I have relinquished my fear of food to a place I can enjoy my life and that’s a wonderful feeling. 

Just a reminder that you can literally enjoy whatever you want, if you have an understanding of what you’re actually eating in your day to day. It’s  living in excess that gets you in trouble.

This is typically how the conversation sounds when people think they have tried a caloric deficit but really have no idea what they are actually eating. Snacks add up!

Science tells us that you WILL lose weight if you are in a caloric deficit (burning more calories than you consume) but frankly, most people are very unaware of what they are eating or how much. 

Before discounting calorie deficit as an ineffective method of losing weight… be honest with yourself. Have you really tracked your food? Is the math mathing? Are you really in a deficit or are you just eating “healthy”? Meaning: you can eat Whole Foods all you want, but just because the foods are whole.. doesn’t mean they are lesser in calories. 

Weight loss is pretty simple.. figure out your maintenance calories.. and create a slight deficit from that consistently over time you will see the weight come off. 

No more “my body is broken/ it doesn’t work for me” excuses. You just aren’t aware of exactly what you are eating! Educate yourself on what calorie deficit is and care enough to make it happen!

By all means listen to your body.. but mine is telling me to move right now. Flow or no flow, catch me in the gym lifting. Never been any other way. Never experienced any negative side effects from it. No I don’t believe you trash your hormones by lifting when on your cycle or miraculously gain weight from lifting a weight during your lady time. 

If you’ll notice I’m a little bloated here, which is NORMAL during my cycle. Don’t let the mumbo jumbo of “wrecking your hormones” keep you from gaining strength every month, month over month ladies. You might feel a little weaker during that time, but I feel moving your body is much better than sitting around for a week. Do you by all means, but building muscle boosts your metabolism.. not slows it.

Self- limiting beliefs are so 2023 💅

Crazy, I know… 

But going absolutely nuts on your diet and nutrition for the remainder of January isn’t the solution to getting fit. ✋🚫

While I love to see people taking action on their health this time of year, it really is fickle to watch 9/10 people discontinue their journey after January is over. 👀

As someone who once was really into super restrictive and all or nothing approaches with fitness, I can tell you.. you’re gonna be disappointed when you figure out that the quick fix or crazy restrictive game is a waste of time and energy. 😩

The solution: ✅

Strength train 3-5 days per week.

Figure out what you are eating! Eat at your maintenance level if you are trying to maintain your fitness, or incorporate a slight caloric deficit if you are trying to lose weight this year. 

Anything else is 🗑️. It really is that simple.. and so much more enjoyable to live life with no worries. 😌
